Looking back on this year in photos and all I see are the little moments with the people I love most.
It’s not the Instagram ready posts that make up life and maybe that’s something I work on sharing more of going forward. 
This year was hard, but I am thankful every day to be building a life well with my people. 
This was the year I got my sewjo back, got my tattoo, learned I suck at riding with a new driver, let go of things that were bringing anxiety instead of peace and let the pieces fall where they were going to fall.
Life is so precious and fleeting, and we focus on and post the pretty moments most but this right here is everything. 
Other moments from this year include: lots of baking, cooking, sewing projects, therapy, reading, swimming, tears, vulnerable conversations that lead to connection and growth, planting a new rose garden and dog hair, always lots of dog hair.
.
.
#2022 #2022reel #2022recap #reels #reellife #reallife #whatmattersmost #family #therapy #healing

Just a little Christmas roundup because it truly was a sweet time together 🥰
We cooked delicious food for Christmas Eve (so that we could have leftovers Christmas Day without having to cook😋), spent time with Jake’s grandpa and a very small candlelight service with traditional Christmas hymns. Always our tradition passed down from my parents to set up cozy beds and sleep by the tree on Christmas Eve, Christmas morning was so peaceful and happy and full of the love that went into each gift, the boys picked me out things that I will use and love all year. The rest of the day was quiet after the boys left and I got in a good cry and Christmas nap before we settled in with leftovers and movies and huskies and a long call with my sister who was also without her kid’s Christmas night😌❤️
Savoring these special moments and the love we share🥰
Wishing you all a peaceful and restful week❤️
.
.
#christmas #christmasreels #reellife #reallife #happychristmas #specialmoments #life #reels #fullheart

It’s been a long year already. 
Anyone else feel that too?
I have been harshly criticized for my life choices, my parenting and my walk with Jesus. 
I brushed it off the first time, but the second time and the digging in of heels the third time and I’ll be honest it’s shaken me. Not because it’s true, but because it is so far from the truth of who I am and what I have built my life to stand for. If you truly know me, you know my life is wrapped up in being a mom to my three boys, loving my people well and being gracious, you know like Jesus. These comments tell me more about the people who said them than they do about myself. It’s hard to have grace for others when your life is wrapped up in fear and judgment. I can’t change other people and I can’t make them see what they don’t want to see. But I can take this as yet another life lesson of “how NOT to be”. I can be an encouragement and safe space for others, especially family where we are meant to be understood, accepted and held JUST AS WE ARE. I can ask my closest and dearest friends how they see me, and let me tell you it’s a beautiful thing to be truly seen, understood and valued for who I am not what I do or don’t do, unconditional love. It’s hard to find grace for ongoing hurt and judgment, space is necessary for healing. I have grown a lot in this and no longer accept others opinions when they do not line up with what I know to be true of myself, I am a really great mom (my therapist said it’s my superpower), I know who I am and where I stand in Christ, loved f-ing unconditionally. I might be shaken but nobody can take these truths from me, I will not be moved. 
If this incredibly personal post makes you uncomfortable feel free to move on. My hope is that we all do the work to heal, grow and know our worth and who we are so others can no longer break us. Shake us, yes maybe but never again will they break us.
Love to you all❤️

I’ve been loving reading again. I have a few books going at a time to listen to and read. I whipped this one up in an hour even with the hand stitching which I loved using a deep plum 12 weight from @aurifilthread as a change from black or white. Go check it out and tag this post to save and make later. Wouldn’t this make a sweet gift along with a favorite book?
Ps loved this @katecbowler book #nocureforbeinghuman and her other one #everythinghappensforareasonandotherliesiveloved and I can’t wait to get her newest one out this week as well as her other books, I’m a fan🥰

Stopping to smell my dog on yet another stressful day. 
Do you smell your dog for comfort or is that just me?🤷‍♀️

The sweetest of 16 year olds! 
I learned to be a mom on this boy and now he’s helping me learn to choose joy and trust God more. He’s given me his input on some things and he’s been right. 
When he’s been in the wrong he comes back and apologizes. 
I chose the name Conrad, it means brave, bold or wise counsel and it suits him well. 
He’s been my number 2 since James came along and is a very kind and mostly gracious big brother.
It’s been my greatest blessing to be his mom, watch him grow and be his person to support and encourage who he is. 
Conrad, you are loved unconditionally for who you are not what you do or don’t do. And who you are is wonderful!

A beautiful gift from my dear friend @lisacrafty ❤️❤️❤️
A few years ago I made one of my hst liberty quilts for Lisa, I cut enough blocks to make two quilts so that we would have matching ones. At some point Lisa asked me to send her the rest of the blocks so that she could make my quilt for me. In the meantime we both moved and a whole lot of life happened. When we were together in February with our friend Jenni @sewlavenderstitches guess what Lisa whipped out!? The blocks for this quilt! We were so productive that weekend just talking and sewing the whole time, Lisa put the blocks together and we all sewed a few rows. She backed it with Liberty and added beautiful binding and sent it to me the other week. 
This quilt came at just the right time and couldn’t be more special with the memories sewed into it and so many special fabrics I had long ago used up. Friends who quilt for each other are extra special🥰
Love you girls so much!
.

Letting this soak in today.
Sending tight hugs and love to everyone whose Mother’s Day feels complicated and hard. 
I actually hate this day and I forget how much till it’s here. From complicated relationships to feeling extremely overlooked and un appreciated by people who are meant to see you and know you well (not speaking of my boys).
There can be healing but it means finding those people who see you and value you, it means becoming the mom your kids need no matter how that looks which requires growth and staying soft and sensitive to each child. It means working through the loss of what you needed and don’t have and trying to love and move forward without expectations when there has been no remorse or repair. It means doing the work to mother yourself through healing and compassion and it means seeing other moms and encouraging and supporting them. Maybe most of all it means raising the next generation to do this whole thing better, parenting with secure attachment rather than pressure and expectation and modeling what unconditional love and acceptance means. 
This day feels hard and heavy because motherhood IS hard and heavy and relationships ARE hard and heavy, so as you scroll through all the happy mom/child posts with an ache in your heart, a lump in your throat and maybe even bitterness, know that healing comes but maybe not in the way we hope. 
We are the healing, we are becoming the mothers of change and it is so worth it today and every day.

*thoughts from my heart this morning, because they are valid and possibly relatable. I am so happy if you have an uncomplicated mother experience and I am so sorry if you have an even harder one.

Sharing something non quilting but kind of related.
Over the weekend my niece and I went to an Ed Sheeran @teddysphotos concert. I cried. It was SO good. Music has always been life giving and soul moving for me. I’ve been singing along to his songs for years, through some incredibly hard times: running in the rain and singing along, listening to the words as I cried in bed and mostly just singing along as I sew. There was nothing like singing along with 73,000 people who I’m guessing love him just as much as I do (I hope he felt that love). 
Life has been hard, I’m constantly waiting for the other shoe to drop (and it always does) and I’m taking one day at a time. I’m so glad that December me decided to buy the cheapest tickets and make these plans in hopes that I would still be standing seven months later. This concert couldn’t have come at the end of a more nuts week and I’m so glad for the break in every day life that it offered to me and Lilly. 
I’ve inspired myself to plan more things, because even if all the shoes drop, I’ll still be standing and life is worth living to the fullest even on hard weeks, months and years. I’ll absolutely be going to more of his shows!
@redhead918 thanks for making time for fun with me🥰

This year I’m struggling to embrace the coming fall and winter, it’s bringing back feelings of some really long dark days that I haven’t felt in a couple years. I used to absolutely dread winter because it made me feel even more isolated and cut off when I would be home for days and weeks at a time with sick kids. I know we are past those days and I actually enjoyed the past couple fall/winters.
